content: Artificial lake in Singapore Botanic Gardens **Swan Lake** is an artificial [lake](/wiki/Lake) located at the [Singapore Botanic Gardens](/wiki/Singapore_Botanic_Gardens) in [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore). It was formerly also known as the Main Lake or the First Lake. It was constructed in 1866, shortly after the Gardens formation. It is considered the oldest ornamental water feature in Singapore. - [Symphony Lake](/wiki/Symphony_Lake,_Singapore) - National Orchid Garden - Jacob Ballas Children's Garden This [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) location article is a stub.
